			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">From your description, I'd say the difference between using condoms vs. abortion is a proactive stance vs. a reactive stance.  Using the condom, aside from the other benefits it offers such as protection from diseases, is a proactive choice on the part of the couple.  Both members are actively seeking to prevent a pregnancy BEFORE it happens.  Abortion, or the morning after pill, is a REACTIVE approach, something that's done after the fact to correct a certain condition, in this case, a pregnancy.
<br />

<br />
Is there really a big difference between the two?  Probably not.  Except the proactive approach at least indicates a modicum of responsibility on the part of the couple, because they start out knowing the consequences of their actions, and try to prevent it.  The couple that defers to abortion or morning after pill appears to have less responsiblity for their actions, deferring any responsible actions until after a pregnancy has occured.
<br />

<br />
- Maige<br />_________________<br /><b><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=52912>Maige Denugget</a></b>
<br />
Master of the Elements
<br />
Arch Mage of the GNOMISH kind
<br />

